parties: In the Matter of Alfonso A. TUMINI Petition for Reinstatement.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM:
Report and Recommendations of Disciplinary Board dated January 9, 1990, accepted, and the Petition for Reinstatement is granted. Pursuant to Rule 218(e), Pa.R.D.E., petitioner is directed to pay the expenses incurred by the Board in the investigation and processing of the Petition for Reinstatement.
McDERMOTT, J., did not participate in the consideration or decision of this case.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM:

attorneys: Gail M. Richman, Philadelphia, for petitioner.
Stephanie Resnick, Louis W. Fryman, Philadelphia, for respondent.
